  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesized that sympatholytic effect of dexmedetomidine would attenuate
      the hemodynamic instability and decrease in the splanchnic blood flow caused by
      pneumoperitoneum during laparoscopic surgery. This study is to investigate the effect of
      intraoperative dexmedetomidine infusion on postoperative bowel movement in patients
      undergoing laparoscopic gastrectomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
